Learn how methinks uses your personal information

Your login details, including your login method, is used exclusively for establishing your connection to the methinks service and will never be shared with, or authorize sharing of your information with, any third party.
Your core profile data is shown to businesses and researchers so that they can get a basic idea of who you are; this helps businesses and researchers to determine if you’re a good fit for their gigs.

Beyond your core profile, you also may have completed other portions of your profile (extended core, lifestyle, gaming, shopping, etc.); this information allows businesses and researchers to more specifically target niche gigs with very specific criteria to thinkers.

Your payment information (and any e-mail address associated with it) is used only by methinks and the payment service to make sure you get paid; this information is never shown to business or researchers and your e-mail is only used to link your methinks account with the payment service.
When you review a business, your review is submitted anonymously and impacts their aggregate rating score; businesses will not be aware of how you rated them.
What to do once you’ve landed a gig

After you’ve applied to a gig, a researcher or business will review your application and, if you’re a good fit, will invite you to join the study. Once you’re invited, check the proposed time, duration, and other requirements for the study and make sure they work for you. If the time doesn’t work and you want to suggest a different time, request a schedule change or message the researcher directly with questions (go to the gig from your home screen, select the message icon, and send a message).

Just like you, businesses and researchers are busy and are making time specifically to work with you on methinks; make sure you show up to your interview or app test a few minutes before the actual start time so that you can get started on time. Depending on the gig, you can join the interview through the methinks app or a computer by going to methinks.io in the Google Chrome browser.

Whether you are participating in an interview or testing an app, a strong WiFI connection and a full battery is vital to ensure that businesses and researchers can receive your thoughts; make sure to test your connection before you start your gig and have your phone or computer plugged in so that you can have a productive session.

Businesses and researchers want your honest thoughts and opinions about their products and ideas, even if they are critical or negative; be courteous, but also tell the truth about your impressions of various products and services you test - negative feedback can help businesses to improve their products if they understand your thinking.

After you’ve successfully completed a gig, please allow up to one week before you receive payment; if you do not see your payment after one week, go to the menu on the top left of the home screen of the thinker app, select “contact us”, set the subject to “billing issue”, and let us know you need to get paid!

Showing up late is bad enough, but completely missing a session is unacceptable; if you no-show, you will be flagged and will not be able to apply for more gigs until you address why you no-showed and commit to not no-showing again. We want the methinks platform to be a supportive and enjoyable part of your life, but it’s not fair to businesses and researchers if you don’t show up when they’ve set time to work with you. If you have a gig scheduled and it turns out you can’t make it, let us know in advance and we’ll help you reschedule (go to the gig from your home screen, select the message icon, and send us a message)!
